properties.areaDesc: Maalaea Bay; Big Island Southeast Waters; Alenuihaha Channel; Pailolo Channel; Big Island Leeward Waters
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 18 at 3:30PM HST until February 20 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, east winds 25 to 35 kt, with higher
gusts, and seas 8 to 13 feet expected. For the Small Craft
Advisory, northeast winds 20 to 30 kt, with higher gusts, and
seas 7 to 12 feet.

* WHERE...Maalaea Bay, Pailolo Channel, Alenuihaha Channel, Big
Island Leeward Waters and Big Island Southeast Waters.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from midnight tonight to 6 PM HST
Thursday. For the Small Craft Advisory, until midnight HST
tonight.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Warning means winds of 34 to 47 knots are imminent or
occurring. Operating a vessel in gale conditions requires
experience and properly equipped vessels. It is highly
recommended that mariners without the proper experience seek safe
harbor prior to the onset of gale conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT HST TONIGHT... ...GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 6 PM HST THURSDAY
